==Maisa's messenger==
* {{tcond|If the player has enough inventory space:}}
** '''Messenger:''' Hello there. I have a message for you.
** {{tbox|pic=Maisa's message detail.png|You've been given a message.}}
** {{tact|end}}
* {{tcond|If the player has no inventory space:}}
** '''Messenger:''' Hello there. I have a message for you, but you'll need to make some room for it.
** {{tact|end}}

==Entering Jaltevas==
===Entering the pyramid===
* '''Maisa:''' Hey! You made it.
* '''Player:''' I came as soon as I could. What are we dealing with?
* '''Maisa:''' Up here? Not a lot. The Devourer must be deeper inside.
* '''Player:''' Well then I guess that's where we're going as well.
* '''Maisa:''' We shouldn't leave this entry unguarded. The Devourer still has plenty of servants out in the desert who we won't want coming in after us.
* '''Player:''' Hmm... fair point. Alright, you keep an eye on things up here while I go after Amascut.
* '''Maisa:''' I had a feeling you might say that, so I made some preparations.
* '''Player:''' Preparations?
* '''Maisa:''' Indeed. The Devourer has made plenty of enemies, and there are others willing to help us. Before you head deeper into the tomb, you might want to consider grouping up with some of them.
* {{tbox|You can enter a raid of the Tombs of Amascut in parties of up to eight people. To form a party or join an existing one, use the Grouping Obelisk.}}
* '''Player:''' I might just do that. Anything else I should know?
* '''Maisa:''' It seems Osmumten had various magical protections built into his tomb. It looks like the Devourer disabled them, which should make things easier for you.
* {{tbox|Before entering a raid, you can customise the difficulty of the challenges you'll face by using Invocations. Invocations can be enabled or disabled from the Grouping Obelisk. There are a large variety of Invocations available, covering both challenge-specific mechanics as well as raid-wide systems.}}
* {{tbox|Enabling or disabling Invocations will change the Raid Level. On top of the Invocation effects, increasing the Raid Level will also increase the stats of all foes in the raid. However, higher Raid Levels will result in more rewards becoming available.}}
* '''Player:''' Alright, I'd better not waste any more time. Amascut may well have already found the two weapons. If so, she'll already be draining the lesser gods of their power.
* '''Maisa:''' Meaning the longer we wait, the stronger she gets. If we don't stop her attaining true godhood, who knows what will happen.
* '''Player:''' We'll stop her.
* '''Maisa:''' Oh, I almost forgot, I found this journal that might be worth a read.
* {{tcond|If the player has no inventory space:}}
** {{tbox|pic=Akila's journal detail.png|Maisa shows you a journal.}}
** '''Maisa:''' Just let me know if you want it.
** {{tact|continue}}
* {{tcond|If the player has one free inventory space:}}
** {{tbox|pic=Akila's journal detail.png|Maisa gives you a journal.}}
* '''Player:''' Thanks. I'd better get ready.
* '''Maisa:''' Good luck.
* {{tact|end}}

===Talking to Maisa===
* '''Maisa:''' Hey.
* {{tselect|Select an Option}}
* {{topt|What do I need to be doing?}}
** '''Player:''' What do I need to be doing?
** '''Maisa:''' The Devourer has all four of the lesser gods somewhere in this tomb. We have to assume she's already found the two weapons she seeks as well.
** '''Player:''' Which means she'll already be draining the lesser gods of their power.
** '''Maisa:''' Exactly. You need to head deeper into the tomb, free the lesser gods and stop the Devourer before it's too late.
** '''Maisa:''' This won't be an easy fight, so make sure you're well prepared. Thankfully, the Devourer is not short of enemies. If needs be, you can use the obelisk here and find some allies to join you.
** '''Player:''' I might just do that.
** {{tact|other}}
* {{topt|Do you have that journal from earlier?}}
** '''Player:''' Do you have that journal from earlier?
** {{tcond|If the player has no inventory space:}}
*** '''Maisa:''' I do, but you'll need to make some room for it.
*** {{tact|end}}
** {{tcond|If the player has inventory space:}}
*** '''Maisa:''' I do. Here you go.
*** {{tbox|pic=Akila's journal detail.png|Maisa gives you a journal.}}
*** {{tact|end}}
** {{tcond|If the player has [[Akila's journal]] in their inventory:}}
*** '''Maisa:''' Don't you already have it?
*** '''Player:''' Ah, so I do. Never mind.
*** {{tact|end}}
* {{topt|I'd better get going.}}
** '''Player:''' I'd better get going.
** '''Maisa:''' Good luck.
** {{tact|end}}

==Path of Apmeken==
===Upon defeating Ba-Ba===
* '''Apmeken:''' You did it! I wasn't sure I'd make it out of that one, but I'm glad you proved me wrong. Come, let's get out of here.
* {{qact|Apmeken and the player return to the Nexus}}
* {{tact|end}}

==Path of Crondis==
===Upon defeating Zebak===
* '''Crondis:''' Amascut's hold on me is finally at an end. Human, let us return to the Nexus.
* {{qact|Crondis and the player return to the Nexus}}
* {{tact|end}}

==Path of Het==
===Upon defeating Akkha===
* '''Het:''' Even with everything we're going through, I have to admit, that was an impressive fight to behold! I wish I could have joined you, friend. Now, let us return to the Nexus.
* {{qact|Het and the player return to the Nexus}}
* {{tact|end}}

==Path of Scabaras==
===Upon defeating Kephri===
* '''Scabaras:''' The... the noise! Her voice in my head for so long, and now... silence! It's so loud! Please, we must leave!
* {{qact|Scabaras and the player return to the Nexus}}
* {{tact|end}}

==The Nexus==
===Apmeken===
====Initial dialogue====
* '''Player:''' Hi there. How are you doing?
* '''Apmeken:''' Oh, you know, just getting over years of being controlled by a deranged family member. All part of the fun in a family like ours, I guess.
* '''Player:''' You seem quite jolly about it all.
* '''Apmeken:''' Well as I always say, 'the real winner is the one smiling.' What Amascut has done is horrific, but it's not too late to stop her. I won't let her get me down, not while there's still hope.
* {{tcond|If the other Avatars of Tumeken have not been freed yet:}}
** '''Apmeken:''' Anyway, I'm annoyingly a bit too weak to help you much down here. However, I reckon if you can free the others, we'll be able to open the way to the lower level for you.
** {{tact|end}}
* {{tcond|If all of the other Avatars of Tumeken have been freed:}}
** '''Apmeken:''' Anyway, we've been able to open the way for you! I wish we could help you down there, but we're still too weak. Don't worry though, I know you can do it!
** {{tact|end}}

====Subsequent dialogue====
* {{tcond|If the other Avatars of Tumeken have not been freed yet:}}
** '''Apmeken:''' I'm annoyingly a bit too weak to help you much down here. However, I reckon if you can free the others, we'll be able to open the way to the lower level for you.
** {{tact|end}}
* {{tcond|If all of the other Avatars of Tumeken have been freed:}}
** '''Apmeken:''' We've been able to open the way for you! I wish we could help you down there, but we're still too weak. Don't worry though, I know you can do it!
** {{tact|end}}

===Crondis===
====Initial dialogue====
* '''Crondis:''' Human.
* '''Player:''' Not feeling talkative?
* '''Crondis:''' I'm sure you will find a conversation with me more appealing than one with Scabaras. Still, I leave most of the talking to Apmeken.
* {{tcond|If the other Avatars of Tumeken have not been freed yet:}}
** '''Crondis:''' Now, I can't support you in your fight, but if you can free the others, we'll be able to open the way to Amascut.
** {{tact|end}}
* {{tcond|If all of the other Avatars of Tumeken have been freed:}}
** '''Crondis:''' Now, we've opened the way to Amascut, but we can do no more. From here, it's up to you.
** {{tact|end}}

====Subsequent dialogue====
* {{tcond|If the other Avatars of Tumeken have not been freed yet:}}
** '''Crondis:''' Human, I can't support you in your fight, but if you can free the others, we'll be able to open the way to Amascut.
** {{tact|end}}
* {{tcond|If all of the other Avatars of Tumeken have been freed:}}
** '''Crondis:''' Human, we've opened the way to Amascut, but we can do no more. From here, it's up to you.
