===Talking to Maisa before the Avatars of Tumeken depart===
* '''Maisa:''' So this is a new one. There's a bunch of lesser gods standing just over there. You should probably go and talk to them.
* {{tact|end}}

===Talking to the Avatars of Tumeken===
* '''Apmeken:''' Here [he is/she is/they are]!
* '''Het:''' My friend, you managed what few have ever achieved. You overcame Amascut herself! I wish I could have been there to see it!
* '''Player:''' Well I couldn't have done it alone. Speaking of which, where's Scabaras?
* '''Crondis:''' Scabaras walks his own path. Do not consider his absence an insult. This is his way.
* '''Het:''' Not to mention that he was under Amascut's control far longer than the rest of us. It will take him time to come to terms with his role in her plots.
* '''Apmeken:''' Don't worry, he'll be okay. He always is.
* '''Het:''' Before we go any further... We didn't have much time for conversation back in the tomb. I'm sure you have some questions for us.
* '''Crondis:''' If you do, now is the time to ask them.
* {{tselect|Select an Option}}
* {{topt|I have a question for Apmeken.}}
** '''Player:''' I have a question for Apmeken.
** {{tselect|Select an Option}}
** {{topt|What's your role in the Menaphite Pantheon?}}
*** '''Player:''' What's your role in the Menaphite Pantheon?
*** '''Apmeken:''' I'm Tumeken's avatar of companionship! Tumeken himself was always considered a bit cold, which is a tad ironic when you think about it.
*** '''Player:''' A cold sun god?
*** '''Apmeken:''' Exactly! Bit odd, right? Still, although he wasn't exactly known for his social side, he still understood the importance of such things. That's why he made me!
*** '''Apmeken:''' My job is to make sure everyone remembers the importance of friendship. After all, we all need a friend or two, or ten, or maybe hundreds! Have as many as you want! I won't judge.
*** {{tact|other}}
** {{topt|Why aren't there more monkeys or apes in the desert?}}
*** '''Player:''' Why aren't there more monkeys or apes in the desert?
*** '''Apmeken:''' Ah, you can thank Amascut for that. The desert used to be home to thousands of apes and monkeys, but she targeted them to try and get to me.
*** '''Player:''' I'm sorry.
*** '''Apmeken:''' Don't be! Now that I'm back, I know we can turn things around!
*** {{tact|other}}
** {{topt|Actually, I've changed my mind.}}
*** '''Player:''' Actually, I've changed my mind.
*** '''Apmeken:''' Fair enough.
*** {{tact|initial}}
** {{topt|I'll be back soon.}}
*** '''Player:''' I'll be back soon.
*** '''Apmeken:''' We'll be here when you're ready.
*** {{tact|end}}
* {{topt|I have a question for Crondis.}}
** '''Player:''' I have a question for Crondis.
** {{tselect|Select an Option}}
** {{topt|What's your role in the Menaphite Pantheon?}}
*** '''Player:''' What's your role in the Menaphite Pantheon?
*** '''Crondis:''' I am Tumeken's avatar of resourcefulness.
*** '''Player:''' Meaning?
*** '''Crondis:''' Meaning my job is to guide the people of the desert not to live lives of excess.
*** '''Player:''' Guessing you're not a fan of Menaphos then?
*** '''Crondis:''' Much of the desert has forgotten the importance of modesty in my absence, but the situation in Menaphos is definitely the most concerning. Let us hope it can soon be rectified.
*** {{tact|other}}
** {{topt|Why are crocodiles so rude?}}
*** '''Player:''' Why are crocodiles so rude?
*** '''Crondis:''' Rude? How so.
*** '''Player:''' Well they always try to eat me when I go near them.
*** '''Crondis:''' The life of a crocodile is not an easy one. They must seek food wherever it is available.
*** '''Crondis:''' Besides, I sense you do not speak the whole truth. Did you not befriend a crocodile yourself in times past?
*** '''Player:''' You mean Roger! I guess he was quite friendly.
*** '''Crondis:''' Then perhaps crocodiles are not as rude as you think.
*** {{tact|other}}
** {{topt|Actually, I've changed my mind.}}
*** '''Player:''' Actually, I've changed my mind.
*** '''Crondis:''' As you wish.
*** {{tact|initial}}
** {{topt|I'll be back soon.}}
*** '''Player:''' I'll be back soon.
*** '''Crondis:''' We will be here.
*** {{tact|end}}
* {{topt|I have a question for Het.}}
** '''Player:''' I have a question for Het.
** {{topt|What's your role in the Menaphite Pantheon?}}
*** '''Player:''' What's your role in the Menaphite Pantheon?
*** '''Het:''' I am Tumeken's avatar of health, both physical and mental.
*** '''Player:''' You talk about strength and fighting a lot. Surely fighting isn't good for someone's health.
*** '''Het:''' Well when it comes to health, is strength not the ultimate goal? The strongest individual is one who is healthy in both body and mind, and what better way to celebrate that strength than in combat!
*** '''Player:''' I guess, but what about those who aren't strong?
*** '''Het:''' Well health is not something to be hoarded, is it? Most weaknesses can be overcome, and it is the duty of the strong to help those less fortunate.
*** '''Player:''' So they can become strong and healthy themselves?
*** '''Het:''' Exactly!
*** {{tact|other}}
** {{topt|Do you have more followers than the others?}}
*** '''Het:''' An interesting question. Why do you ask?
*** '''Player:''' Considering you have a human appearance, I wondered if that might resonate more with people.
*** '''Het:''' Not as much as you might think. Believe it or not, in some ways, I'm actually considered a bit boring! Why follow the human when you have a baboon god?
*** '''Apmeken:''' Especially when the baboon god is so fun to be around!
*** '''Het:''' Of course, people just following one of us was never really the intention anyway. We're a pantheon, and we all have a part to play.
*** '''Het:''' Now that Amascut is running with her tail between her legs, perhaps we can remind people of that.
*** {{tact|other}}
** {{topt|Actually, I've changed my mind.}}
*** '''Player:''' Actually, I've changed my mind.
*** '''Het:''' Very well.
*** {{tact|initial}}
** {{topt|I'll be back soon.}}
*** '''Player:''' I'll be back soon.
*** '''Het:''' We'll wait for you to return.
*** {{tact|end}}
* {{topt|I have a question for all of you.}}
** '''Player:''' I have a question for all of you.
** {{tselect|Select an Option}}
** {{topt|What will happen with Amascut?}}
*** '''Player:''' What will happen with Amascut?
*** '''Het:''' I'd say that's up to her. If she doesn't change her ways, her fate won't be pretty.
*** '''Apmeken:''' But it's never too late for redemption. There might still be hope for her.
*** '''Crondis:''' Whatever path she takes, we will be ready.
*** '''Player:''' Do you really think she'd change her ways at this point?
*** '''Crondis:''' It seems unlikely, but there is one who might be able to change that.
*** '''Player:''' Who?
*** '''Apmeken:''' Icthlarin! If anyone can help Amascut find her way again, it's him!
*** '''Player:''' He doesn't seem to have been doing much to help so far.
*** '''Het:''' Icthlarin is limited in what he can do. His duties to the dead require constant attention.
*** '''Apmeken:''' Not to mention the pact!
*** '''Player:''' Pact?
*** '''Crondis:''' That is not for us to discuss.
*** '''Apmeken:''' Oh yes, sorry. Maybe we should talk about something else.
*** {{tact|other}}
** {{topt|Are you actually gods?}}
*** '''Player:''' Are you actually gods?
*** '''Het:''' If you asked a citizen of these lands, I'm sure they'd probably say yes.
*** '''Crondis:''' Indeed, but they would not be truly correct.
*** '''Player:''' How so?
*** '''Apmeken:''' Tumeken made us using his own divine essence! Each of us is a piece of him!
*** '''Crondis:''' But that does not make us gods. While great, our power is insignificant compared to a true god. That is why they are gone, and we remain.
*** '''Player:''' So what are you really?
*** '''Het:''' You might hear some refer to us as the Avatars of Tumeken. We'd consider that a more fitting title.
*** '''Player:''' What about Icthlarin and Amascut?
*** '''Apmeken:''' Tumeken made them too. Difference is, they also have some of Elidinis' divine essence, making them a lot more powerful!
*** '''Crondis:''' But again, they are not true gods.
*** '''Het:''' Amascut was hoping to change that today, but you showed her where to stick that plan!
*** {{tact|other}}
** {{topt|Actually, I've changed my mind.}}
*** '''Player:''' Actually, I've changed my mind.
*** '''Apmeken:''' Fair enough.
*** {{tact|initial}}
** {{topt|I'll be back soon.}}
*** '''Player:''' I'll be back soon.
*** '''Apmeken:''' We'll be here when you're ready.
*** {{tact|end}}
* {{topt|So what happens now?}}
** '''Player:''' So what happens now?
** '''Crondis:''' We are the Avatars of Tumeken, and the Kharidian Desert has been without guidance for too long. It is time we fixed that.
** '''Apmeken:''' We're going to get started right away!
** '''Het:''' But don't worry, we don't intend to miss the fight against Amascut. I hope you'll stand alongside us when that day comes.
** '''Crondis:''' For now though, this is goodbye. We will meet again, human.
** '''Apmeken:''' It was great to meet you. Thank you for helping us!
** {{tbox|The avatars depart.}}
** {{tact|end}}
* {{topt|I'll be back soon.}}
** '''Player:''' I'll be back soon.
** '''Het:''' We'll wait for you to return.
** {{tact|end}}

