** '''Maisa:''' You're back! I just had an interesting chat with a group of lesser gods. Seems you dealt a heavy blow to the Devourer and made some powerful new friends in the process.
** '''Player:''' It didn't go perfectly. Amascut still escaped, and she'd already gained a fair amount of power by that point.
** '''Maisa:''' True, but things could have wound up going a lot worse. You're right though, this is clearly far from over.
** '''Player:''' Where do you think she'll have gone? Menaphos?
** '''Maisa:''' Most likely. She didn't go to all the effort of causing those plagues for nothing. This tomb was clearly only part of her plan.
** '''Maisa:''' Still, she'll need to reconsider her strategy after her defeat. We have a little time now.
** '''Player:''' Hopefully time for the city to reopen again. What will you do in the meantime?
** '''Maisa:''' The lesser gods were under the Devourer's control for a long time, and a lot's changed since they disappeared. I've offered to help them where I can.
** '''Player:''' Then I guess this is goodbye for now.
** {{tcond|If the player does not have the [[Antique lamp (Into the Tombs)|Antique lamp]] in their inventory:}}
*** '''Maisa:''' Indeed, but before I go, I have something for you.
*** {{tbox|pic=Antique lamp (Into the Tombs) detail.png|Maisa gives you an antique lamp.}}
*** '''Player:''' Thanks!
*** '''Maisa:''' Don't mention it. Now, take care of yourself out there.
*** {{tact|continue}}
** {{tcond|If the player talks to Maisa after having the [[Antique lamp (Into the Tombs)|Antique lamp]] in their inventory or after using the lamp:}}
*** '''Maisa:''' Indeed. Take care of yourself out there.
*** {{tact|continue}}
** '''Player:''' And you.
** {{tbox|Maisa departs.}}
** {{tact|end}}

